practices.name: Primary Care Holistic Medical Clinic
practices.description:
We, at To be Primary Care Holistic Medical Clinic, take a pride at helping patients who haven’t been able to regain their health through traditional medical methods.  Whether you are battling chronic illnesses such as hashimoto, headache, allergies or gut issues, or you are not feeling as healthy as you used to be, we are here to help you.

Our approach is different. Not only that we will take a hard look at your symptoms, but we will also make sure that we understand your mental, emotional and nutritional well being, as all of them play an important role in your overall health.  Based on our evaluation, we will provide you with personalized treatment plan that will work just for you.  Together, as a team, we will work with you to regain your health

profile.title: MD
profile.bio:
Dr. Thao Nguyen chose medicine as her profession after experiencing a bout of illness that mystified the top doctors at a famous east coast hospital. Dr. Thao felt alone and desperate being treated in a medical system that seemed mechanical in its approach to her care. She felt her doctors probed and prodded but never stopped long enough to understand her symptoms or fears. She grew hopeless as each successive test result returned with no answers and it was apparent her doctors were hopeless too. Through this experience, Dr. Thao promised to never give up on her patients, to always look for another way. This promise would launch her onto a path of exploration to discover that we are more than flesh and bone.

By conventional measures, Dr. Thao excelled in her medical training. She graduated with honors from UC Davis School of Medicine, and served as chief resident at the prestigious University of California, San Francisco.   However, she became deeply saddened as she sat with patients who were afflicted with chronic illnesses. She often felt, “my patients are ‘stuck’ and the medications I give them imprison them more!”

At about this time Dr. Thao met two esteemed healers, Donna Eden and Scott Walker. They showed her how to work with the human energy vital force, and our emotional network. Physical symptoms sometimes dissolved in minutes using their healing methods.

The people who taught Dr. Thao the most, however, were her patients. They showed her how each person is unique in their expression of illnesses and thus different in our responses to treatment. Dr. Thao realized, there is no magic cure-all pill. Her patients taught her to be more open-minded when helping them heal and reminded her of the sense of wholeness. They demonstrated how powerful the mind can be and how it can affect the body.

Since 2001, Dr. Thao has worked as a primary care physician in a variety of settings: From the slums of Kenya to the inner city of San Francisco; from private practice to Indian Health Services. She also received additional training in Functional Medicine and Ayurveda at the Scripps Institute.

Today, she uses medications when it is appropriate. She also incorporates foods as medicine, acupressure, and low level laser to treat a wide range of illnesses in family medicine. She has special interests in skin rejuvenation, autoimmune diseases and mood disorders.

Dr. Thao’s favorite meal is soup and she loves to read mystery novels. During her time off, you might find her doing pilates and yoga in Los Gatos
